ptr[x] ^= 255;
is correct for full-range pictures, sure. But shouldn't the range be taken into consideration? The results look very different when the wrong range is used – and the vast majority of videos uses the limited "MPEG" range.

The problem is that with limited range, luma values < 20 are invalid when inverted, i.e. luminance is clipped. Maybe it is safer to expand the range to full first, then invert:
if(image->_range == ADM_COL_RANGE_MPEG)
    image->expandColorRange();

